# Commitzen Format

Use this commit format for every commit in this repo:

`<domain>(<goal>): <summary>`

- `domain` = area of intent (e.g., `core`, `tests`, `docs`, `config`, `rules`, `meta`)
- `goal` = short purpose phrase (e.g., `bootstrap`, `harden`, `document`, `refine`)
- `summary` = imperative, concise description of the change

Examples:
- `docs(document): add agent commit guidance`
- `core(bootstrap): add Jira scanning pipeline`
- `tests(bootstrap): add guardrails unit coverage`
